sentences: Shizuko Kasagi (笠置 シヅ子, Kasagi Shizuko, 25 August  1914 – 30 March 1985) was a popular Japanese jazz singer and actress.
Shizuko Kasagi was born Shizuko Kamei (亀井 静子) on 25 August 1914 in Ōkawa District, Kagawa, Japan.
She appeared in the 1948 film Drunken Angel directed by Akira Kurosawa.
In 1955, Shizuko retired from singing and concentrated on her acting career.
Kasagi died from ovarian cancer on 30 March 1985, aged 70.
